{
  "texts": [
    "This also verifies the deterministic-random trade-off within ISAC systems.",
    "Receive signal processingAs pointed out by [154], the time-varying radar waveform within a coherent processing interval results in range sidelobe modulation (RSM) of clutter, which poses a challenge in clutter mitigation by reducing target visibility.",
    "Several receive signal processing techniques have been proposed to deal with this problem.",
    "For example, Sahin et al. [155] used the mismatched filter to mitigate the RSM.",
    "In addition, O'Connor et al. [156] addressed the RSM by jointly designing the pulse compression coefficients during a coherent processing interval."
  ]
}